    "department": "Growth",
    "description": "ABOUT SUNO\n\nWe're building the world's first platform for creating and discovering original music, including Suno Studio, a generative audio workstation, and Hooks, a new way to create and share videos that bring songs to life.\n\nPowered by the leading music-creation model and designed to amplify imagination, our platform makes it possible for anyone to turn inspiration into music. With Suno, ideas flow into sound, songs become yours, and everyone can experience the joy of creating.\n\n\nSuno is one of the fastest-growing AI startups in the world, backed by leading investors including Menlo Ventures, Lightspeed Venture Partners, Matrix, NVentures, and Hallwood Media.\n\nFounded in 2023 by Harvard alumni with a shared passion for music, Suno has empowered more than 100 million people to create original songs. In 2025, we raised a $250 million Series C to accelerate product innovation and international growth.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nSuno is growing fast, and paid social creative is a major driver of that growth. The right person for this role takes Suno's brand identity and pushes it into performance creative that earns attention and converts – work that drives growth and brings the excitement of using Suno to everyone who sees it.\n\n\n\nThis is a hybrid graphic and motion design role on the performance marketing (i.e. paid social media advertising) team. You'll own the branded paid social creative pipeline: conceiving, producing, and iterating on work across static and motion formats. You'll work closely with the performance marketing team, treating data and channel insights as creative inputs rather than afterthoughts. Over time, you'll help build the workflows and systems that let us scale without losing what makes Suno's creative distinctive. As the team grows, there's a path to managing other creative contributors.\n\n\n\nCheck out the song we made about it: https://suno.com/s/dDrWV7XNe6I5mJax\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Translate Suno's brand identity and creative DNA into paid social creative that drives growth across paid channels (Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, etc.)\n\n - Own the full branded creative pipeline – concepting, producing, and iterating on static and motion assets\n\n - Build and maintain a creative roadmap: what to make, what to test, what to push further, and what to move on from\n\n - Partner with the performance marketing team to use data and channel feedback as creative inputs, not just outputs\n\n - Use AI tools to extend creative output beyond what's manually possible – and help build the processes and guardrails that keep AI-assisted work on-brand and up to Suno's standards\n\n - Develop workflows and production processes that scale creative output without diluting brand quality\n\n - Help shape how the next generation of creators discovers Suno – the creative you make is often their first impression\n   \n   \n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL NEED\n\nMust-Haves\n\n - 4+ years of marketing design experience, including designing assets for paid social media advertising campaigns (i.e. performance creative)\n\n - Portfolio of paid social work (static and motion) that demonstrates both craft and taste for great performance creative\n\n - Experience at a marketing/advertising agency or a high-growth B2C/DTC company\n\n - Hybrid graphic and motion design skills: strong static design fundamentals and real motion/animation capability – this is not a pure graphic design role\n\n - Expert-level proficiency in Figma, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, and After Effects\n\n - Fluency in what makes paid social creative work: hooks, formats, platform conventions, and what drives meaningful iteration\n\n - Ability to internalize a brand's visual identity and push it into new formats without losing what makes it distinctive\n\nNice-to-Haves\n\n - Hands-on experience with AI-assisted creative tools (generative image, video, or copy) as part of a real production workflow\n\n - Background in music, entertainment, or creator-focused consumer products\n\n - Experience managing or mentoring junior creative contributors\n   \n   \n\nAdditional Notes\n\nApplicants must be eligible to work in the US. This role is expected to work from the designated Suno office 5 days a week.\n\n\n\n\nPERKS \u0026 BENEFITS FOR FULL-TIME EMPLOYEES\n\n - Company Equity Package\n\n - 401(k) with 3% Employer Match \u0026 Roth 401(k)\n\n - Medical, Dental, \u0026 Vision Insurance (PPO w/ HSA \u0026 FSA options)\n\n - 11 Paid Holidays + Unlimited PTO \u0026 Sick Time\n\n - 16 Weeks of Paid Parental Leave\n\n - Creative Education Stipend\n\n - Generous Commuter Allowance\n\n - In-Office Lunch (5 days per week)\n\nSuno is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We consider qualified applicants without regard to race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, marital or family status, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other legally protected basis under provincial, federal, state, and local laws, regulations, or ordinances. We will also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the requirements of state and local laws, including the Massachusetts Fair Chance in Employment Act, NYC Fair Chance Act, LA City Fair Chance Ordinance, and San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
